<subSubSection id="D2AD57C1F30203A2E2BF2E3229BB08CC" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="88F7A4049F4070BF3C4957935B13AC95" pageNumber="451">
Etymology L 
<taxonomicName id="BE67D961AE62756E45C26F93442C893F" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181899" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole melastomae Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole melastomae Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="451" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melastomae">melastomae</taxonomicName>
, referring to the preferred melastome nesting site.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="29107EE5E4B1FF3F2AF7D6F621EA2E06" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="04A43A2066E89B8D16699B2570617598" pageNumber="451">
Diagnosis A medium-sized, yellow member of the 
<taxonomicName id="35B2B56A08CD9F5067D4D68FFECC770C" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33744" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole flavens Roger" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole flavens Roger" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="451" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavens">flavens</taxonomicName>
group characterized by a nearly complete absence in major and minor of sculpturing anywhere behind the anterior half of the head, the reduction of the propodeal spine to an obtuse angle, the very small size of the propodeal spiracle, shallow occipital concavity in full-face view, and abundant long pilosity. The major is further distinguished by its overall flattened mesosomal dorsal profile and laterally angulate postpetiole. Similar species: 
<taxonomicName id="F9AAEA94B0CA1585CBEB1DE53509EE07" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181837" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole amabilis Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole amabilis Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="451" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amabilis">amabilis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="DCA5B2F4198F65460E67FB3EF39F2AFE" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181845" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole boliviana Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole boliviana Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="451" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boliviana">boliviana</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="EDEABDE07AB6E07ABF4FB81EB73FDC9F" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181905" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole mixteca Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole mixteca Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="451" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mixteca">mixteca</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="6C414E80E168AC32048EF760E8D1435A" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181940" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole scitula Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole scitula Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="451" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scitula">scitula</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="630762124209B3A830C2E0078300A017" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34052" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole terresi Wheeler &amp; Mann" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole terresi Wheeler &amp; Mann" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="451" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terresi">terresi</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="F0FF1F878BEB96DEF857D9EF764AEF02" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34074" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole tysoni Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole tysoni Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="451" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tysoni">tysoni</taxonomicName>
. Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 0.80, HL 0.84, SL 0.42, EL 0.10, PW 0.42. Paratype minor: HW 0.44, HL 0.46, SL 0.42, EL 0.06, PW 0.24.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="31F1B18947FCC5E95DE41D6774993F8A" type="description">
<paragraph id="0408EBE48B8339D6AECD96A80D5B3A7C" pageNumber="451">color Major: body mostly clear medium yellow, with dorsum of head and mandibles brownish yellow. Minor: concolorous light to medium yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="21F25D5347D87C392922DE37431FA73E" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="4ACBAEB34024EE6323CD472803B50139" pageNumber="451">Range Known from the type locality in Panama and from Colombia (near San Jose, Choco, localities in Valle) and Ecuador (Endesa, Pichincha).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="70C370942E268132D1FE44442BD86E5F" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="278EB836DEFB4E92FAD8A514FF55A7D7" pageNumber="451">Biology Hilly rainforest, nesting in myrmecophytic melastomes (Leeanne Tennant-Alonso in Panama and Colombia). Winged males were present in a nest in Colombia in early June and in Panama in early July.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CB9A2CE350E7C5943E6A6BD03EB7A5CA" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="1B0066B31B255A35C0E23D34437C1F5C" pageNumber="451">Figure Upper: holotype, major. Lower: paratype, minor. PANAMA: Estacion Nusagandi, Comarca de Kuna Yala, 350 m (Leeanne Tennant-Alonso). Scale bars = 1 mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
